In [16]:
# Optimize K
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
def optimal_kmeans(dataset,normalized_dataset,start=2,end=11):
    n_clu = []
    km_ss = []
    for n_clusters in range(start,end):
        kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters)
        labels = kmeans.fit_predict(normalized_dataset)
        silhouette_avg = round(silhouette_score(dataset,labels,random_state=1),3)
        km_ss.append(silhouette_avg)
        n_clu.append(n_clusters)
        print('NO.Clusters : {}   ,Silhouette Score : {}'.format(n_clusters,silhouette_avg))
    if n_clusters == end -1 :
        plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
        plt.title('Silhouette Score')
        sns.pointplot(x=n_clu,y=km_ss)

In [18]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

# Scale the data
X = data[['Part of Body','Nature']] # Features
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Apply K-means algorithm
kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=4, random_state=42)
kmeans.fit(X_scaled)

# Cluster labels
labels = kmeans.labels_

# Compute cluster centers
cluster_centers = scaler.inverse_transform(kmeans.cluster_centers_)

# Analyze cluster features
features = X.columns
for i, center in enumerate(cluster_centers):
    print(f"Cluster {i+1}:")
    for j, feature in enumerate(features):
        print(f"Feature {feature}: {center[j]}")

# Analyze labels
data['Cluster Label'] = labels
cluster_labels_1 = data.groupby('Cluster Label')['Hospitalized_binary'].unique()
cluster_labels_2 = data.groupby('Cluster Label')['Amputation_binary'].unique()
for i, labels_1 in cluster_labels_1.iteritems():
    print(f"Cluster {i+1}: Hospitalization: {labels_1}")

for i, labels_2 in cluster_labels_2.iteritems():
    print(f"Cluster {i+1}: Amputation: {labels_2}")

# Visualize clustering
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)
plt.scatter(X_pca[:, 0], X_pca[:, 1], cmap='viridis', c=data['Cluster Label'])
plt.xlabel('First Principal Component')
plt.ylabel('Second Principal Component')
plt.title('Clustering with K-means')
plt.show()

7.1.1 Cluster 1¶

In [20]:
cluster_1 = cluster[cluster['Cluster Label']==0]
In [21]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8,8))

size = 0.5
Hospitalized_binary_vals = cluster_1["Hospitalized_binary"].value_counts()
labels_Hospitalized_binary =  ['Not Hospitalization', 'Hospitalization']

Amputation_binary_vals = cluster_1["Amputation_binary"].value_counts()
labels_Amputation_binary =  ['Amputated','Not Amputated']

cmap = plt.colormaps["tab20c"]
outer_colors = cmap([1, 2, 5, 6, 9, 10])

ax[0].pie(Hospitalized_binary_vals, radius=1, colors=outer_colors, labels=labels_Hospitalized_binary, autopct="%1.1f%%", shadow=True,
       wedgeprops=dict(width=size, edgecolor='w'))
ax[0].set_title("Hospitalization or Not Hospitalization")

ax[1].pie(Amputation_binary_vals, radius=1, colors=outer_colors, labels=labels_Amputation_binary, autopct="%1.1f%%", shadow=True,
       wedgeprops=dict(width=size, edgecolor='w'))
ax[1].set_title("Amputated or Not Amputated")
plt.tight_layout()

fig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(20,20))

sns.countplot(data=cluster_1 , x='Part of Body Title', ax=ax[0],order = cluster_1['Part of Body Title'].value_counts().index).tick_params(axis="x", labelrotation=90)
ax[0].set_title('Cluster 1 Part of Body Titles')

sns.countplot(data=cluster_1 , x='NatureTitle', ax=ax[1],order = cluster_1['NatureTitle'].value_counts().index).tick_params(axis="x", labelrotation=90)
ax[1].set_title('Cluster 1 Nature Titles')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
